<div class="columns">
    <div class="column"></div>
    <div class="column">

        <h2 class="title is-2 has-text-centered">Create a new batch</h2>

        <div class="box has-text-centered">
            <%= form_for @batch do |f| %>
                <%= f.text_area :urls, class: "textarea mb-5", placeholder: "Insert Google Doc URLs here (one per line)" %>
                <%= f.submit class: "button is-success is-fullwidth" %>
            <% end %>
        </div>

        <div class="notification">
            <h2 class="title is-3 mb-5 has-text-centered">Instructions</h2>
            <p>Place your guest post URLs in the text area above. Keep one on each line. Make sure each document has <b>"Anyone with this link can edit"</b> permissions.</p></br>
            <p>Once you hit "Create Batch," the app will retrieve data from each file and present you with a summary on the next page.</p></br>
            <p><b>Important: </b>The files you attempt to analyze using this app must be in native Google Docs format. If you input .docx files, you will get an error.</p>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div class="column"></div>
</div>